  "folder": "fhSubModern00001",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>A pale powder folded into rolling papers and chewed under the tongue. Modern street name for a recipe older than streets — the same blend of crushed seeds and synthetic alkaloids surfaces in every city's quieter corners under a different name each year.</p><p><strong><em>Desired effects on use.</em></strong> For 30 minutes you have advantage on Wisdom (Insight) checks and Wisdom (Perception) checks that rely on hearing.</p><p><strong><em>On use, save against addiction.</em></strong> Make a DC 12 Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, you gain the Addicted condition from Whisperdust (see below).</p><p><strong><em>Addicted from Whisperdust.</em></strong> While you have this Addicted condition, you are also Poisoned and have disadvantage on Wisdom saving throws (background voices keep pulling at your attention).</p><p><strong><em>Withdrawal Modifier: 2.</em></strong> Withdrawal lasts max(2 &minus; your Constitution modifier, 1) long rests, minimum 1.</p><p><em>Requires: Rolling Papers.</em></p>"
    },
